description: Racers compete in a 2 mile time trial on Kreitler Rollers with Killer Headwind fan and flywheel.  Timed with Roller Fusion.  Two up race format.
course: 2 miles on rollers timed with Roller Fusion, no rerides.
registration: Day of registration only.  Cost is $15, juniors $5.  Non-USCF must buy a 1-day license
notes: This is the final race in the Iowa Roller Championship Series.  Championship medals will be awarded after racing concludes and results are tabulated.  Your 3 best times averaged from 3 different races constitute your state championship time. The drawing for the rollers will also be held after the medals are awarded.  To be eligible you must have compete in at least 4 different races.  Each race you do is an entry, minimum 4, maximum 8.
directions: Straight west of the Ames S Duff Target, up the hill behind Panera Bread.

title: Race Like A Girl
description: Series of track-style races held on a closed loop at Union Park. A and B races for men, women\'s race, and kid\'s races. Family friendly and casual race vibe.
course: A paved loop about 0.5 miles in length with one small hill. No 90 degree corners.
registration: $10 for Men, $5 for Women, Kid\'s race free (but must have helmets).
notes: If time permits there will be up to 3 races for each category, plus the kid\'s race.
directions: Union Park in Des Moines off Penn Avenue, just north of University.
